  "description": "Sqrt2 constant with LFO1 sweeping depth at a medium rate (1.8 Hz) across the full Pell sequence: 1/1, 3/2, 7/5, 17/12, 41/29, 99/70, 239/169, 577/408. As depth sweeps, partials staircase through successively closer rational approximations to √2. Unlike Pi or E cascades, the Pell sequence has a musical logic: each step is a convergent of a tritone (√2 is exactly the equal-temperament tritone). The cascade sounds like a tritone hunting its own identity — always approaching, never arriving. Medium-high filter cutoff (16000 Hz) reveals each convergent fully as it passes. LFO2 counter-rotates partial phases to prevent the sweep from becoming repetitive. This is the tritone as a living thing.",
